  mmm: {"title":"Marketing Mix Model (MMM) · Budget Optimization","desc":"Fits each channel's spend-revenue response curve using adstock (carryover) and saturation (diminishing returns) to derive each channel's contribution, current marginal ROAS, and saturation level. Enter a total budget to optimally allocate toward channels with higher marginal returns and maximize forecasted revenue.","demoNote":"Demo environment — explore features with synthetic curves. In production, fitting uses collected performance data.","anomTitle":"Anomaly Detection (SPC) · Real-time Alerts","anomMethod":"Method: control charts (μ±σ) plus Western Electric rules (±3σ / runs) applied to each channel's ROAS·CPA·spend·CTR·CVR time series. Detects sudden shifts and drift statistically, without policies.","aiTitle":"AI Insight Report","aiDesc":"Combines MMM, anomaly detection, and performance data to generate an executive summary, root causes, and recommended actions in natural language.","aiGenerating":"Generating…","aiGenerate":"Generate AI Report","empty":"Performance data is not yet sufficient. Once you run and collect channel data, response curves are fitted automatically.","optTitle":"Predictive Budget Optimization","dailyBudget":"Total Daily Budget (KRW)","curDaily":"Current Daily Spend Total","optimizing":"Optimizing…","optimize":"Calculate Optimal Allocation","predCurrent":"Forecast Monthly Revenue (Current Allocation)","predOpt":"Forecast Monthly Revenue (Optimal Allocation)","lift":"Expected Revenue Lift","channel":"Channel","current":"Current Daily Budget","recommended":"Recommended Daily Budget","change":"Change","marginalRoas":"Marginal ROAS","saturation":"Saturation","fit":"Fit (R²)","contribShare":"Contribution Share","currentRoas":"Current ROAS","satHigh":"Saturated — low efficiency on additional spend","satLow":"Headroom — high efficiency when increased","satMid":"Optimal range","method":"Method: least-squares fit of an adstock (geometric decay λ) + saturation (β·(1−exp(−x/κ))) curve to each channel's daily spend→revenue data. Marginal ROAS = dRev/dSpend; optimization = greedy marginal allocation over concave curves.","nowMarker":"Now","sevCritical":"Critical","sevWarning":"Warning","recActionLabel":"Recommended Action","daysUnit":"days","aiByClaude":"Generated by Claude AI","aiRuleBased":"Rule-based Summary"},
