    guideStep3Desc: "Analyze costs, target margins, price elasticity, and channel characteristics to calculate recommended selling prices for each channel.\n\nFactors Included\n• Product Cost\n• Target Margin Rate\n• Price Elasticity\n• Channel Fees\n• VAT\n• Competitive Pricing\n\nResults Provided\n• Recommended Selling Price\n• Estimated Margin\n• Estimated Revenue\n• Estimated Sales Volume\n\nResult\nYou can identify the most profitable selling price for each channel.",
    guideStep4Phase: "Phase B · Price Analysis",
    guideStep4Title: "Pricing Scenario Simulation",
    guideStep4Desc: "Analyze the potential impact of price changes before applying them.\n\nSimulation Metrics\n• Revenue Changes\n• Sales Volume Changes\n• Margin Changes\n• Net Profit Changes\n\nExamples\n• 5% Price Increase\n• 10% Price Reduction\n• Competitive Response Pricing\n\nResult\nYou can validate pricing strategies before deploying them in live operations.",
    guideStep5Phase: "Phase C · Channel Strategy",
    guideStep5Title: "Optimize Channel Mix",
    guideStep5Desc: "Adjust pricing and sales allocation across channels to maximize overall profitability.\n\nAnalysis Metrics\n• Channel Profitability\n• Sales Distribution\n• Customer Characteristics\n• Fee Structure\n\nResult\nYou can identify which channels deserve greater investment and focus.",
    guideStep6Phase: "Phase C · Channel Strategy",
    guideStep6Title: "Apply Channel Fees",
    guideStep6Desc: "Calculate actual profitability by incorporating channel fees and VAT.\n\nIncluded Costs\n• Sales Commission\n• Advertising Fees\n• Settlement Fees\n• VAT\n\nResult\nYou can accurately calculate net margins based on actual settlement amounts.",
    guideStep7Phase: "Phase C · Channel Strategy",
    guideStep7Title: "Monitor Competitor Pricing",
    guideStep7Desc: "Track competitor pricing to evaluate your market competitiveness.\n\nAnalysis Metrics\n• Competitor Prices\n• Price Change History\n• Lowest Price Status\n• Market Average Price\n\nResult\nYou can objectively assess your pricing competitiveness in the market.",
    guideStep8Phase: "Phase D · Automation",
    guideStep8Title: "Dynamic Repricer",
    guideStep8Desc: "Automatically adjust prices based on predefined pricing rules.\n\nAutomation Triggers\n• Inventory Levels\n• Competitor Pricing\n• Demand Changes\n• Promotion Schedules\n\nResult\nPrices are automatically optimized according to market conditions.",
    guideStep9Phase: "Phase D · Automation",
    guideStep9Title: "Pricing Calendar",
    guideStep9Desc: "Manage price change schedules for promotions and seasonal events.\n\nManagement Items\n• Discount Campaigns\n• Seasonal Promotions\n• Event Pricing\n• Scheduled Price Changes\n\nResult\nYou can execute pricing strategies in a structured and consistent way.",
    guideStep10Phase: "Phase D · Automation",
    guideStep10Title: "Real-Time Synchronization",
    guideStep10Desc: "Price changes are instantly reflected across all connected systems.\n\nSynchronization Scope\n• Sales Channels\n• Dashboards\n• Settlement Systems\n• Analytics Reports\n\nResult\nAll systems operate using the same pricing data and standards.",
    guideStep11Phase: "Phase E · Operations & Security",
    guideStep11Title: "Performance Monitoring",
    guideStep11Desc: "Continuously track the performance of your pricing strategy.\n\nMetrics to Monitor\n• Revenue\n• Margin\n• Sales Volume\n• Adoption Rate\n• ROI\n\nResult\nYou can continuously improve and re-optimize your pricing strategy.",
    guideStep12Phase: "Phase E · Operations & Security",
    guideStep12Title: "Security & Access Management",
    guideStep12Desc: "Protect cost and pricing information with enterprise-grade security controls.\n\nSecurity Features\n• Tenant Data Isolation\n• Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)\n• Access Logs\n• Data Encryption\n• Anomaly Detection\n\nResult\nSensitive pricing and cost data is securely protected and managed.",
    guideTip1: "Enter logistics and fulfillment costs accurately to improve pricing recommendation reliability.",
    guideTip2: "Set target margin rates based on fee differences across sales channels.",
    guideTip3: "Pricing recommendations become more accurate as elasticity data accumulates.",
    guideTip4: "Review competitor pricing at least once per week.",
    guideTip5: "Always configure a minimum margin threshold when using Dynamic Repricing.",
    guideTip6: "Validate pricing strategies through simulations before applying them.",
    guideTip7: "Use the Pricing Calendar to systematically manage promotion schedules.",
    guideTip8: "Recalculate optimal prices whenever channel fees change.",
    guideFaqTitle: "Frequently Asked Questions",
    guideFaq1Q: "How are optimal selling prices calculated?",
    guideFaq1A: "Recommended prices are calculated by analyzing product costs, target margins, price elasticity, channel fees, VAT, and competitor pricing for each sales channel.",
    guideFaq2Q: "What costs are included in the product cost?",
    guideFaq2A: "Actual costs are automatically calculated by combining purchase costs with inbound, outbound, storage, labor, and shipping expenses.",
    guideFaq3Q: "Why are recommended prices different across channels?",
    guideFaq3A: "Each channel has different fees, VAT requirements, competitive environments, and demand characteristics, resulting in different optimal prices.",
    guideFaq4Q: "Can Dynamic Repricing reduce prices below my margin threshold?",
    guideFaq4A: "No. Prices will never be adjusted below the minimum allowed margin that you configure.",
    guideFaq5Q: "How is competitor pricing collected?",
    guideFaq5A: "Competitor prices and pricing history are collected regularly from connected channels and monitoring sources.",
    guideFaq6Q: "Will price changes be reflected in other modules?",
    guideFaq6A: "Yes. Price changes are synchronized in real time across sales channels, dashboards, settlement systems, and analytics reports using a single source of truth.",
    guideSecurityTitle: "Security & Privacy",
    guideSecurityDesc: "Sensitive business data, including costs, prices, and margins, is protected with enterprise-grade security.\n\nSecurity Policies\n• Tenant-Level Data Isolation\n• Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)\n• Access Logging\n• Encryption in Transit and at Rest\n• Anomaly Detection\n• Minimal Collection of Sensitive Information",
    guideOpsTitle: "Recommended Operational Reviews",
    guideOpsDesc: "Review the following items regularly to ensure stable pricing operations.\n\nDaily Reviews\n• Monitor competitor price changes\n• Verify Dynamic Repricing activity\n\nWeekly Reviews\n• Review channel margins and optimal price adoption rates\n• Evaluate simulation results\n\nMonthly Reviews\n• Update cost data\n• Retrain price elasticity models\n• Review channel fee structures",
    guideReadyTitle: "You're Ready to Get Started",
    guideReadyDesc: "Register your products and costs, then calculate your first optimal selling price.\n\nRecommended Workflow\nRegister Products & Costs → Calculate Optimal Prices → Apply Channel Fees → Validate Scenarios → Enable Dynamic Repricing → Monitor Performance\n\nOnce price optimization is implemented, you can automatically maintain the most profitable selling price for each channel while improving both margins and revenue.",
