    "guideTip5": "Configure carrier integrations before processing outbound shipments.",
    "guideTip6": "Maintain safety stock levels to prevent stockouts.",
    "guideTip7": "Schedule regular cycle counts to ensure inventory accuracy.",
    "guideTip8": "Use low-stock alerts and automatic replenishment to avoid inventory shortages.",
    "guideFaqTitle": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "guideFaq1Q": "Can I manage multiple warehouses?",
    "guideFaq1A": "Yes. The system supports multiple warehouses, zones, racks, and storage locations under a single platform.",
    "guideFaq2Q": "What happens if received quantities differ from the purchase order?",
    "guideFaq2A": "You can record discrepancies during inbound inspection and adjust inventory accordingly.",
    "guideFaq3Q": "How does order consolidation work?",
    "guideFaq3A": "Orders with the same recipient can be automatically grouped and shipped together in a single package.",
    "guideFaq4Q": "Which shipping carriers are supported?",
    "guideFaq4A": "The platform supports major domestic and international carriers including CJ Logistics, Hanjin, Lotte, FedEx, DHL, UPS, Yamato, and SF Express.",
    "guideFaq5Q": "How are inventory audits performed?",
    "guideFaq5A": "You can conduct full physical counts or cycle counts and reconcile differences directly within the system.",
    "guideFaq6Q": "Can the system notify me before inventory runs low?",
    "guideFaq6A": "Yes. Safety stock thresholds trigger alerts and automatic replenishment recommendations.",
    "guideSecurityTitle": "Security & Privacy Protection",
    "guideSecurityDesc": "• Tenant-level data isolation\n• Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)\n• Warehouse-specific permission management\n• Comprehensive audit logs\n• Encrypted customer and recipient information\n• Principle of least privilege",
