    "guideLangBadge": "Available in 15 Languages",
    "guideLearnTitle": "What You'll Learn",
    "guideLearnDesc": "By completing this guide, you'll be able to authenticate your sending domain, create responsive email templates, and launch personalized campaigns for specific customer segments.\n\nYou'll also learn how to optimize performance with A/B testing and automation workflows, analyze delivery, open, click, and conversion rates, and manage subscriber consent and unsubscribe requests in compliance with industry regulations.",
    "guideStep1Phase": "Phase A · Getting Started",
    "guideStep1Title": "Connect and Authenticate Your Sending Domain",
    "guideStep1Desc": "Authenticate your sending domain to improve deliverability and sender reputation.\n\nHow to proceed\n1. Register your sending domain.\n2. Configure SPF, DKIM, and DMARC records.\n3. Set up sender name and email address.\n4. Verify authentication status.\n5. Save your settings.\n\nOutcome\nYour domain is authenticated, reducing spam classification risks and improving email deliverability.",
    "guideStep2Phase": "Phase A · Getting Started",
    "guideStep2Title": "Verify Sender Profile",
    "guideStep2Desc": "Review sender information and email delivery settings.\n\nChecklist\n• Sender Name\n• Sender Email Address\n• SPF, DKIM, and DMARC Status\n• Return-Path Configuration\n• Sending Limits\n\nOutcome\nYour sender profile is validated and ready for production email delivery.",
    "guideStep3Phase": "Phase B · Content Preparation",
    "guideStep3Title": "Create Email Templates",
    "guideStep3Desc": "Build reusable responsive email templates.\n\nComponents\n• Drag-and-Drop Builder\n• HTML Editor\n• Header, Body, and Footer Sections\n• Buttons, Images, and Links\n• Mobile-Responsive Layouts\n\nOutcome\nReusable email templates are ready for future campaigns.",
    "guideStep4Phase": "Phase B · Content Preparation",
    "guideStep4Title": "Personalize Content",
    "guideStep4Desc": "Use customer data and dynamic content blocks to personalize emails.\n\nExamples\n• Customer Name Personalization\n• Membership Tier Content\n• Product Recommendations\n• Conditional Content Blocks\n\nOutcome\nEach recipient receives a personalized email experience.",
    "guideStep5Phase": "Phase B · Content Preparation",
    "guideStep5Title": "Use AI Creative Studio",
    "guideStep5Desc": "Generate email subject lines, content, and visuals using AI.\n\nFeatures\n• Subject Line Generation\n• Email Copy Creation\n• Image Generation\n• Tone Optimization\n• Content Length Optimization\n\nOutcome\nCreate high-quality email content without requiring specialized design resources.",
    "guideStep6Phase": "Phase C · Audience Targeting",
    "guideStep6Title": "Connect CRM Segments",
    "guideStep6Desc": "Import CRM customer segments to build targeted recipient groups.\n\nExamples\n• VIP Customers\n• Repeat Buyers\n• Dormant Customers\n• New Subscribers\n\nOutcome\nHighly targeted audiences are prepared for campaign delivery.",
    "guideStep7Phase": "Phase C · Audience Targeting",
    "guideStep7Title": "Validate Consent and Filter Recipients",
    "guideStep7Desc": "Verify subscriber consent and clean recipient lists before sending.\n\nValidation Items\n• Marketing Consent Status\n• Unsubscribed Contacts Exclusion\n• Duplicate Removal\n• Invalid Address Removal\n• Bounce List Exclusion\n\nOutcome\nA compliant and optimized recipient list is finalized.",
    "guideStep8Phase": "Phase D · Campaign Execution",
    "guideStep8Title": "Create and Launch a Campaign",
    "guideStep8Desc": "Combine templates and audience segments to launch email campaigns.\n\nHow to proceed\n• Select a Template\n• Choose Recipients\n• Create Subject Line\n• Add Preview Text\n• Send Immediately or Schedule Delivery\n\nOutcome\nYour campaign is successfully delivered to the target audience.",
    "guideStep9Phase": "Phase D · Campaign Execution",
    "guideStep9Title": "Run A/B Tests",
    "guideStep9Desc": "Compare variations to improve campaign performance.\n\nTest Elements\n• Subject Lines\n• Send Times\n• Email Content\n• CTA Buttons\n• Design Variations\n\nOutcome\nThe best-performing version can automatically be selected and deployed.",
    "guideStep10Phase": "Phase D · Campaign Execution",
    "guideStep10Title": "Set Up Automation Workflows",
    "guideStep10Desc": "Automate email delivery based on customer behavior.\n\nExamples\n• Welcome Email Series\n• Abandoned Cart Recovery\n• Post-Purchase Follow-Up\n• Re-engagement Campaigns\n\nOutcome\nRepetitive tasks are automated and emails are delivered at the right time.",
    "guideStep11Phase": "Phase E · Operations & Security",
    "guideStep11Title": "Analyze Performance",
    "guideStep11Desc": "Measure campaign results and continuously improve performance.\n\nKey Metrics\n• Delivery Rate\n• Open Rate\n• Click-Through Rate (CTR)\n• Conversion Rate\n• Revenue\n• ROI\n• Bounce Rate\n• Unsubscribe Rate\n\nOutcome\nIdentify the highest-performing content and audience segments.",
    "guideStep12Phase": "Phase E · Operations & Security",
    "guideStep12Title": "Manage Security and Unsubscribes",
    "guideStep12Desc": "Protect subscriber data and manage unsubscribe requests in compliance with regulations.\n\nSecurity Features\n• Tenant Data Isolation\n• RBAC Access Control\n• One-Click Unsubscribe\n• Consent History Management\n• Audit Logs\n• Data Encryption\n\nOutcome\nA secure and compliant email marketing environment is maintained.",
    "guideTip1": "Always configure SPF, DKIM, and DMARC before sending campaigns.",
    "guideTip2": "Keep subject lines concise and compelling.",
    "guideTip3": "Make full use of preview text.",
    "guideTip4": "Personalize emails using customer data.",
    "guideTip5": "Send test emails before launching campaigns.",
    "guideTip6": "Continuously run A/B tests.",
    "guideTip7": "Manage inactive subscribers separately.",
    "guideTip8": "Optimize templates based on performance insights.",
    "guideFaqTitle": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "guideFaq1Q": "Why is domain authentication important?",
    "guideFaq1A": "It improves sender reputation and email deliverability while reducing spam filtering.",
    "guideFaq2Q": "How is the open rate measured?",
    "guideFaq2A": "Open rates are tracked automatically through email tracking pixels.",
    "guideFaq3Q": "How is click-through rate measured?",
    "guideFaq3A": "Clicks are tracked automatically through link tracking technology.",
    "guideFaq4Q": "How are unsubscribe requests handled?",
    "guideFaq4A": "Unsubscribed recipients are automatically excluded from future campaigns.",
    "guideFaq5Q": "Why do email deliveries fail?",
    "guideFaq5A": "Common causes include invalid addresses, authentication issues, spam filtering, and full mailboxes.",
    "guideFaq6Q": "Can CRM contacts be used immediately?",
    "guideFaq6A": "Yes. CRM segments can be imported and used immediately after consent verification.",
    "guideSecurityTitle": "Security & Privacy",
    "guideSecurityDesc": "Subscriber information and email delivery data are protected by enterprise-grade security controls.\n\nSecurity Policies\n• Tenant Data Isolation\n• RBAC Access Control\n• Consent Management\n• Unsubscribe Management\n• Audit Logging\n• Encryption at Rest\n• Encryption in Transit\n• Data Minimization",
    "guideOpsTitle": "Recommended Operational Reviews",
    "guideOpsDesc": "Review the following items regularly to maintain a healthy email program.\n\nDaily Reviews\n• Delivery and Bounce Monitoring\n• Domain Authentication Status\n\nWeekly Reviews\n• Open, Click, and Conversion Analysis\n• Spam Complaint and Unsubscribe Trends\n\nMonthly Reviews\n• Template Optimization\n• Inactive Subscriber Cleanup\n• Permission and Access Reviews",
    "guideReadyTitle": "You're Ready to Get Started",
