    "securityBannerTitle": "🛡️ Security Threat Detected",
    "connectedLabel": "Connected",
    "guideSub": "The Product Listing Center is a unified commerce management platform that enables businesses to publish products, manage pricing, synchronize inventory, and automate operations across domestic and global sales channels using a single product catalog. By following this guide, even first-time users can successfully complete product onboarding, channel registration, pricing configuration, inventory synchronization, and automation setup.",
    "guideBeginnerBadge": "Beginner Friendly",
    "guideTimeBadge": "Est. Setup Time: 10 Minutes",
    "guideLangBadge": "Supports 17 Sales Channels",
    "guideWhereToStart": "Where Should I Start?",
    "guideWhereToStartDesc": "1. Navigate to Commerce → Product Listing Center from the left navigation menu.\n2. Connect your sales channels through the Integration Hub.\n3. Select products from the Catalog.\n4. Configure channel-specific pricing.\n5. Map product categories and publish products.\n6. Enable automatic synchronization for pricing and inventory management.",
    "guidePhaseA": "Phase A. Getting Started",
    "guideStep1Title": "Verify Login and Environment",
    "guideStep1Desc": "After opening the Product Listing Center, verify the current working environment.\n• Production: Products will be published to live sales channels.\n• Demo: Safe environment for testing and training.\nIf you are using the system for the first time, it is recommended to practice in the Demo environment before switching to Production.",
    "guideStep2Title": "Connect Sales Channels",
    "guideStep2Desc": "Register channel API credentials through the Integration Hub.\n[Required Credentials] API Key · API Secret · Seller ID\n[Domestic Channels] Coupang · Naver Smart Store · 11st · Gmarket · Kakao · Cafe24 · Wemakeprice · Interpark · Lotte ON · Direct Store\n[Global Channels] Shopify · Amazon · TikTok Shop · Rakuten · Lazada · Qoo10 · Zalando\nOnce connected, products can be published and synchronized automatically.",
    "guideStep3Title": "Review the Catalog",
    "guideStep3Desc": "Review publishable product information in the Catalog tab.\n[Available Information] Product name · SKU · Cost · Sale price · Category · Stock quantity · Brand information\nUse category filters or search to quickly select target products.",
    "guidePhaseB": "Phase B. Channel Registration",
    "guideStep4Title": "Select Products and Start Publishing",
    "guideStep4Desc": "Select the products to publish, then run [Publish to Channel].\n[Supported Functions] Product publishing · Product removal · Simultaneous multi-channel publishing · Bulk publishing\n[Displayed Information] Number of selected products · Average cost · Estimated sale price · Estimated revenue",
    "guideStep5Title": "Set Channel-Specific Pricing",
    "guideStep5Desc": "Recommended sale prices are calculated automatically based on platform fees, VAT, and target margin.\n[Recommended Price Formula] Sale Price = Cost ÷ (1 − Fees − VAT − Target Margin)\n[Supported Functions] Channel-specific pricing · Bulk price application · Margin-based auto calculation · Exchange-rate-based global pricing\nYou can adjust the sale price individually per channel if needed.",
    "guideStep6Title": "Manager Approval and Publishing",
    "guideStep6Desc": "Review the registration details on the final review screen.\n[Review Items] Sales channel · Number of products · Estimated revenue · Estimated profit · Margin rate\nDepending on the permission policy, publishing proceeds after manager approval.",
    "guidePhaseC": "Phase C. Price and Inventory Sync",
    "guideStep7Title": "Bulk Price Editing",
    "guideStep7Desc": "You can edit the prices of large product volumes at once.\n[Supported Methods] Fixed price · Markup (%) · Discount (%) · Target margin\nThousands of products can be processed simultaneously.",
    "guideStep8Title": "Set Price Rules and Inventory Policy",
    "guideStep8Desc": "Configure operational rules for automatic synchronization.\n[Price Rules] Automatic margin · Exchange-rate linkage · Competitor price matching · Minimum margin protection\n[Inventory Policy] Safety stock · Automatic out-of-stock handling · Channel stock allocation · Stock priority management\nPrices and inventory are synchronized automatically based on the configured rules.",
    "guidePhaseD": "Phase D. Category Mapping and Execution",
    "guideStep9Title": "Category Mapping",
    "guideStep9Desc": "Map your product categories to the sales channel categories.\n[Supported Methods] AI auto mapping · Recommended mapping · Manual mapping\n[Note] Products without completed category mapping may be rejected by channels. It is recommended to verify all categories before publishing.",
    "guideStep10Title": "Run Synchronization",
    "guideStep10Desc": "Send data to the sales channels from the Sync Execution tab.\n[Synced Data] Product information · Sale price · Stock quantity · Category information · Product attributes\nThe data is applied to the selected channels in bulk.",
    "guidePhaseE": "Phase E. Monitoring and Automation",
    "guideStep11Title": "Monitor Job History",
    "guideStep11Desc": "Review registration results in the Job History tab.\n[Available Statuses] Success · Failed · In progress · Retry · Canceled\nFailed jobs can be analyzed through detailed logs.",
    "guideStep12Title": "Automatic Sync and Notification Setup",
    "guideStep12Desc": "Activate automated operation features.\n[Supported Functions] Scheduled sync · Failure alerts · SLA monitoring · Automatic retry · Operational alerts\nAutomation enables stable 24/7 product operations.",
    "guideTip1": "Complete category mapping before publishing products.",
    "guideTip2": "Keep each channel's fees and VAT information up to date.",
    "guideTip3": "Use bulk price editing to quickly adjust overall margins.",
    "guideTip4": "Apply safety stock policies to prevent out-of-stock exposure.",
    "guideTip5": "For global channels, reflect exchange rates and estimated duties in the sale price.",
    "guideFaqTitle": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "guideFaq1Q": "Can I use the system without connecting channels?",
    "guideFaq1A": "You can browse the interface, but actual product publishing and synchronization require channel integration.",
    "guideFaq2Q": "My product publishing is rejected.",
    "guideFaq2A": "Check category mapping, required attributes, and product image registration.",
    "guideFaq3Q": "Can I apply different prices per channel?",
    "guideFaq3A": "Yes. You can set them individually using the channel price Override function.",
    "guideFaq4Q": "Stock quantities differ from the channel.",
    "guideFaq4A": "Please check your inventory policy and synchronization interval.",
    "guideFaq5Q": "How is the recommended sale price calculated?",
    "guideFaq5A": "It is calculated automatically based on cost, platform fees, VAT, and target margin.",
    "guideSecurityTitle": "Security and Access Control",
    "guideSecurityDesc": "Publishing permissions can be separated through a manager approval process.\nRBAC role-based access control · SSO single sign-on · Two-factor authentication (2FA) · IP access control · Audit logs · Data encryption · API access control",
    "guideOpsTitle": "Operational Recommendations",
    "guideOpsDesc": "[Daily] Sync failures · Out-of-stock products · Price-deviation products\n[Weekly] Channel margin analysis · Category mapping status · Publishing success rate\n[Monthly] Channel profitability analysis · New channel expansion review · Operational policy optimization",
    "guideReadyTitle": "Ready! Publish Your First Product to Multiple Channels",
    "guideReadyDesc": "Catalog review → Channel registration → Pricing setup → Automatic synchronization. Manage product listing, pricing, and inventory across 17 domestic and global sales channels with a single product catalog.",
