    "supTitle":"Suppression List","supDesc":"Unsubscribed, bounced or complaint addresses are permanently excluded from sending. Add/remove manually.","supUnsub":"Unsubscribe","supManual":"Manual","supBounce":"Bounce","supComplaint":"Complaint","supEmpty":"No suppressed addresses","supAddPh":"Email to suppress","supAdd":"Add","supColEmail":"Email","supColReason":"Reason","supColDate":"Date","supRemove":"Remove","cohortTitle":"Cohort Retention (signup month × repeat rate)","cohortDesc":"Repeat-purchase rate of each signup-month cohort over the following months — diagnose loyalty & LTV trends.","cohortEmpty":"No cohort data yet (appears as signup & purchase history accrues).","cohortCol":"Signup month","cohortSize":"Size",
      "segRefresh": "Recompute membership (sync from live data)",

    guideStep1Desc: "To start collecting customer data, connect your sales channels and customer touchpoints.\n\nAvailable Channels:\nOnline Store · Brand Website · Kakao · Email · Messaging Platforms · Marketplaces\n\nSteps:\n1. Open the Integration Hub.\n2. Select a channel.\n3. Enter the required API credentials.\n4. Test the connection.\n5. Save the configuration.\n\nOutcome:\nCustomer records are collected automatically, and order data begins syncing in real time.",
    guideStep2Desc: "Review and manage synchronized customer information from all connected channels.\n\nAvailable Fields:\nName · Email · Phone Number · Membership Tier · Tags · Registration Date · Last Purchase Date\n\nAvailable Actions:\nSearch · Filter · Sort · Export to CSV · Manual Registration\n\nOutcome:\nA centralized customer database is created and continuously maintained.",
    guideStep3Desc: "Customer value and churn risk are evaluated automatically.\n\nRisk Levels:\nCritical · High · Normal\n\nCustomer Segments:\nChampions · Loyal Customers · Potential VIPs · New Customers · At-Risk Customers · Dormant Customers\n\nOutcome:\nIdentify the most valuable and highest-priority customer groups at a glance.",
    guideStep4Desc: "AI analyzes customer behavior and automatically creates actionable customer segments.\n\nExamples:\nVIP Upsell Candidates · Likely Repeat Buyers · At-Risk Customers · High-Value Purchase Customers\n\nAI Insights:\nExpected Conversion Rate · Estimated Revenue · Estimated Audience Size\n\nOutcome:\nQuickly discover high-value customer segments for targeted marketing campaigns.",
    guideStep5Desc: "Create customer segments using your own business rules and conditions.\n\nExamples:\nPurchased Within Last 30 Days · 3+ Purchases · VIP Customers · Customers Located in Seoul\n\nOutcome:\nExecute highly targeted and personalized marketing campaigns.",
    guideStep6Desc: "Measure customer value using industry-standard RFM analysis.\n\nR (Recency):\nHow recently the customer made a purchase\n\nF (Frequency):\nHow often the customer purchases\n\nM (Monetary):\nHow much the customer spends\n\nOutcome:\nCustomer value is scored and categorized automatically.",
    guideStep7Desc: "View a complete customer profile and interaction history.\n\nAvailable Information:\nContact Details · Order Count · Total Revenue · Customer Lifetime Value (LTV) · Visit History · Campaign Engagement History\n\nOutcome:\nDeliver personalized customer experiences based on individual behavior and value.",
    guideStep8Desc: "Send messages to individual customers or customer segments.\n\nSupported Channels:\nEmail · Kakao AlimTalk · Kakao FriendTalk\n\nOutcome:\nLaunch targeted customer engagement and marketing campaigns.",
    guideStep9Desc: "Connect customer segments to automated marketing workflows.\n\nExamples:\n\nNew Customer\n→ Welcome Message\n→ Welcome Coupon\n→ First Purchase Reminder\n\nAt-Risk Customer\n→ Re-engagement Message\n→ Discount Coupon\n→ Win-Back Campaign\n\nOutcome:\nReduce repetitive tasks through automated customer engagement workflows.",
    guideStep10Desc: "CRM data and analytics dashboards operate from a unified data source.\n\nAutomatically Synced:\nNew Customers · Orders · Refunds · Segments · Campaign Performance\n\nOutcome:\nEnsure consistent and up-to-date customer data across the platform.",
    guideStep11Desc: "Measure business performance across customer segments.\n\nKey Metrics:\nRevenue · Conversion Rate · Repeat Purchase Rate · ROAS · Customer Retention Rate\n\nOutcome:\nIdentify the highest-performing customer segments and campaigns.",
    guideStep12Desc: "Protect customer data with enterprise-grade security controls.\n\nSecurity Features:\nTenant Isolation · Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) · Continuous Security Monitoring · Access Logging · Data Minimization Policy\n\nOutcome:\nMaintain secure, compliant, and reliable customer data management.",
    guideFaq1Q: "When are customers collected automatically?",
    guideFaq1A: "Once syncing completes after channel integration, they are collected automatically.",
    guideFaq2Q: "What's the difference between manually registered and auto-collected customers?",
    guideFaq2A: "Only the collection method differs; they are managed identically afterward.",
    guideFaq3Q: "When are segments refreshed?",
    guideFaq3A: "They refresh automatically based on the configured sync interval.",
    guideFaq4Q: "How is at-risk status calculated?",
    guideFaq4A: "AI comprehensively analyzes purchase cycle, activity, spend, and more.",
    guideFaq5Q: "Who can send messages?",
    guideFaq5A: "Only roles permitted by the administrator can send.",
    guideFaq6Q: "Is customer data separated from other companies?",
    guideFaq6A: "Yes — it runs on a fully isolated, per-tenant structure.",
    guideSecurityDesc: "Customer data is logically isolated for each tenant and continuously protected through enterprise-grade security monitoring.\n\nSecurity Controls:\n• Data Minimization Policy\n• Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)\n• Audit Logging\n• Encryption at Rest and In Transit\n• Anomalous Access Detection\n• Tenant-Level Data Isolation",
    guideOpsDesc: "Daily\n• Review newly collected customers\n• Monitor at-risk customers\n\nWeekly\n• Analyze segment performance\n• Review campaign effectiveness\n\nMonthly\n• Re-run RFM analysis\n• Clean up dormant customer records\n• Re-evaluate VIP customer segments\n• Review customer retention trends",
