      guideTitle: "Campaign Management User Guide",
      guideSub: "Learn the complete campaign execution workflow—from setting marketing goals and allocating budgets to preparing creatives, targeting CRM audiences, running A/B tests, and analyzing performance across channels.",
      guideStepsTitle: "Step-by-Step Guide",
      guideStep1Title: "Define Campaign Objectives",
      guideStep1Desc: "Establish campaign goals and key performance indicators before execution.\n\nConfiguration Items\n• Campaign Objective (Awareness, Conversion, Retention, etc.)\n• KPIs (ROAS, Conversions, Revenue)\n• Campaign Duration\n\nOutcome\nClear goals and measurable success criteria are established.",
      guideStep2Title: "Allocate Budget and Channels",
      guideStep2Desc: "Define the total budget and distribute it across channels.\n\nHow to Proceed\n• Set Total Campaign Budget\n• Allocate Budget by Channel (Email, Messaging, Ads, etc.)\n• Define Daily and Lifetime Limits\n\nOutcome\nA structured budget plan is created for efficient campaign execution.",
      guideStep3Title: "Create a Campaign",
      guideStep3Desc: "Create a campaign by entering its core information.\n\nRequired Information\n• Campaign Name\n• Campaign Period\n• Target Channels\n• Goal and Budget Assignment\n\nOutcome\nA campaign is created and ready for execution.",
      guideStep4Title: "Verify Channel Integrations",
      guideStep4Desc: "Confirm that all marketing and communication channels are properly connected.\n\nVerification Checklist\n• Email Integration\n• Messaging Channel Integration\n• Advertising Platform Connections\n• Channel Permissions\n\nOutcome\nAll channels are connected and available for multi-channel execution.",
      guideStep5Title: "Prepare Creatives and Assets",
      guideStep5Desc: "Use AI-powered creative tools to prepare campaign assets.\n\nAvailable Features\n• AI Copy Generation\n• AI Image Generation\n• Channel-Specific Asset Optimization\n• Creative Version Management\n\nOutcome\nCampaign assets are prepared and optimized for each channel.",
      guideStep6Title: "Connect CRM Segments",
      guideStep6Desc: "Select CRM customer segments as campaign audiences.\n\nExamples\n• VIP Customers\n• Repeat Buyers\n• New Customers\n• Dormant Customers\n\nOutcome\nCampaigns are delivered to highly targeted audiences.",
      guideStep7Title: "Approve and Launch Campaign",
      guideStep7Desc: "Review, approve, and launch the campaign.\n\nWorkflow\n• Campaign Review\n• Approval Process\n• Immediate or Scheduled Launch\n\nOutcome\nApproved campaigns are launched across selected channels.",
      guideStep8Title: "Run A/B Tests",
      guideStep8Desc: "Compare multiple variations to maximize campaign performance.\n\nTesting Elements\n• Creatives and Messaging\n• Delivery Timing\n• Landing Pages\n• CTR and Conversion Metrics\n\nOutcome\nThe highest-performing version can be identified and deployed.",
      guideStep9Title: "Monitor Performance in Real Time",
      guideStep9Desc: "Track campaign performance using real-time dashboards.\n\nMetrics\n• Impressions\n• Clicks\n• Conversions\n• ROAS\n• Budget Utilization\n\nOutcome\nCampaign performance can be monitored and optimized immediately.",
      guideStep10Title: "Optimize and Reallocate Budget",
      guideStep10Desc: "Adjust budget allocation based on campaign performance.\n\nOptimization Actions\n• Increase Budget for High-Performing Channels\n• Reduce Spend on Low-Performing Channels\n• Reallocate Across Campaigns\n\nOutcome\nMarketing spend is optimized to maximize ROAS.",
      guideStep11Title: "Analyze Results and Generate Reports",
      guideStep11Desc: "Review campaign outcomes and identify opportunities for improvement.\n\nAnalysis Areas\n• Funnel Analysis\n• Channel Performance\n• ROAS Rankings\n• Campaign Comparisons\n\nOutcome\nThe most effective channels and strategies are identified.",
      guideStep12Title: "Manage Security and Permissions",
      guideStep12Desc: "Protect campaign data and control user permissions securely.\n\nSecurity Features\n• Tenant Data Isolation\n• Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)\n• Approval Workflows\n• Audit Logs\n• Data Encryption\n\nOutcome\nCampaigns and budgets remain secure and fully governed.",
      guideStep13Title: "Lifecycle Management",
      guideStep13Desc: "Manage Draft→Active→Paused→Ended cycle.",
      guideStep14Title: "Data-Driven Decisions",
      guideStep14Desc: "Strategic decisions based on KPI trends.",
      guideStep15Title: "Continuous Optimization",
      guideStep15Desc: "Improve continuously via A/B tests & reviews.",
